quran[26]{c,v,t}:
  23,93,"Say, \"My Lord, if You are going to show me what you have promised them"
  23,94,"then, My Lord, do not place me among such unjust people"
  23,95,We are surely able to show you what We have promised them
  23,96,Overcome evil with good- We are well aware of what they are saying
  23,97,"And say, \"My Lord, I seek refuge in You from the incitements of the devils"
  23,98,"and I seek refuge in You, my Lord, so they may not come near me"
  23,99,"When death comes to one of them, he says, \"My Lord, send me back"
  23,100,"so that I may make amends for what I left undone.\" Never! This is but a word he is saying; for behind them there is a [dimensional) barrier until the Day when all will be resurrected"
  23,101,"So when the Horn is blown, no ties of kinship will bind them on that Day, nor will they ask about one another"
  23,102,"And those whose balance [of good deeds) is heavy, it is they who will be successful"
  23,103,"but those whose balance is light, those are the ones who have lost their souls and will remain in Hell forever"
  23,104,"The Fire will sear their faces, distorting them horribly and painfully"
  23,105,Were not My verses recited to you and did you not reject them
  23,106,"They will say, \"Our Lord, our defiance overcame us, and we were led astray"
  23,107,"Our Lord, get us out of here, and, if we go back to our evil ways, we would be unjust"
  23,108,"He will say, \"Remain despised where you are and do not speak to Me"
  23,109,"Among My worshipers there were those who used to say, 'Our Lord, We have believed, so forgive us and have mercy on us, for You are the most Merciful"
  23,110,"But you were so preoccupied with mocking them that you forgot about Me, while you were laughing at them"
  23,111,I have rewarded them this Day for their patient endurance - they are the successful
  23,112,"He said: \"How many years were you on earth"
  23,113,"They will say, \"We were there a day or part of a day; ask those who keep track of it"
  23,114,"He will say, \"You stayed but a little, if only you had known"
  23,115,"Did you think, then, that We created you in vain, or that you would not be returned to Us"
  23,116,"How sublimely exalted is God, the Ultimate Sovereign, the Ultimate Truth; there is no deity except Him, Lord of the Noble Throne of His majesty"
  23,117,"Whoever calls another deity besides God with no evidence for its existence, then his reckoning will be with his Lord. the unbelievers will never triumph"
  23,118,"And, say, \"My Lord, forgive and have mercy; and You are the most Merciful-to-all"